{
  "text": "The divergence of five B-class MADS-box genes into PI, AP3A1, AP3A2, AP3B1 and AP3B2 subclades with the evolution of the orchid family involved the development of a highly modified perianth consisting of sepals, petals and lip [CITATION_1] ",
